{"sections":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recursive-descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fork-join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each chapter culminates in REPL commands you can try in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"companion sample at ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"},{"text":". By the end you will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have built the same library that backs the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"calc-repl"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"executable, one Cambium subsystem at a time.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"hero","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","overridingTitle":"Get started"}},{"chapters":[{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Build a Lossless CST","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/02-DriveBuilder","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium represents a parsed document as a homogeneous green tree","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whose nodes are tagged with a kind. In this chapter you define the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calculator’s grammar, drive a builder from a recursive-descent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parser, and add Pratt-style precedence and parser-level error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recovery so the resulting tree round-trips even malformed input.","type":"text"}]}]},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Read and Model the Tree","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/04-ReadingTree","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/05-TypedAST","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/06-Evaluator"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once a tree exists, consumers need to walk it, query it by byte","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"position, and project a typed view for kind-specific work. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"chapter introduces borrowed cursors, owned handles, byte-streaming","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text reads, and a typed AST overlay generated from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumSyntaxMacros\/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)"},{"text":" macro, then uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them to build a recursive evaluator.","type":"text"}]}]},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Edit, Reparse, and Memoize","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/07-ReplacementWitnesses","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/08-IncrementalReparse","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/09-AnalysisTranslation"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium’s trees are persistent: editing produces a new tree","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sharing as much green storage as possible, with a witness","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"describing the structural change. This chapter wires up constant","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"folding via subtree replacement, an incremental reparse loop with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a reuse oracle, and memoized analysis caches whose entries","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"survive edits by translating through the witnesses.","type":"text"}]}]},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Concurrency and Persistence","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/10-ForkJoinEval","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/11-ParallelParse","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/12-Serialization"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium’s trees promote into ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshots that are ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and safe to share across tasks. In","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this chapter you write a structured-concurrent fork-join","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"evaluator, parse a workload of expressions in parallel through a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shared token interner, and serialize a tree to disk for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"editor-style warm restarts.","type":"text"}]}]}],"name":null,"image":null,"content":[],"kind":"volume"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reference material that complements the hands-on tutorials.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"resources","tiles":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Articles in the Cambium documentation that complement the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hands-on path:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Getting Started” — narrative skim of the API."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Calculator” — sample-code overview."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Externalized Interning” — deep dive on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TokenInterner"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"identifier":"documentation","title":"Documentation","action":{"title":"View more","destination":"https:\/\/xn--wxa.dog\/cambium\/documentation\/cambium\/","type":"link"}},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The calculator example is a standalone SwiftPM package at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"},{"text":". Each tutorial cites the file in that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example whose canonical implementation it builds toward —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"read them side by side once you have finished the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"corresponding tutorial.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — the full sample."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — REPL command reference."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"identifier":"sampleCode","title":"Sample Code","action":{"title":"View more","destination":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","type":"link"}}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/tableofcontents"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"overview","hierarchy":{"paths":[],"reference":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents"},"metadata":{"category":"Cambium","estimatedTime":"4hr 50min","role":"overview","categoryPathComponent":"TableOfContents","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium"},"references":{"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/12-Serialization":{"title":"Save and Load Trees","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium can serialize a tree to a compact byte stream and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"decode it back. The format is length-, hash-, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"kind-validated at every record, so flipped bytes produce"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"named errors at decode time rather than silently malformed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trees."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/12-Serialization","estimatedTime":"15min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/12-serialization"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/08-IncrementalReparse":{"title":"Incrementally Reparse","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An IDE re-runs the parser on every keystroke. Reparsing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whole document each time is wasteful when most subtrees did"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not change. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental"},{"type":"text","text":" exposes the four pieces"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you wire together for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"subtree-level"}]},{"type":"text","text":" reuse:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession"},{"type":"text","text":" (long-lived"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bookkeeping), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle"},{"type":"text","text":" (the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser-facing query API), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/TextEdit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the change description), and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" (the post-parse summary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of what was reused)."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/08-IncrementalReparse","estimatedTime":"30min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/08-incrementalreparse"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/05-TypedAST":{"title":"Project a Typed AST Overlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium’s CST stores everything as homogeneous nodes tagged"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a kind. That uniformity is what makes editing and reuse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cheap, but it leaves consumers to write "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"switch node.kind { ... }"},{"type":"text","text":" everywhere they want kind-specific behavior."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/05-TypedAST","estimatedTime":"25min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/05-typedast"},"chapter-banner.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/org.cambium.Cambium\/chapter-banner.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"chapter-banner.png","alt":"Chapter banner","type":"image"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/02-DriveBuilder":{"title":"Drive a GreenTreeBuilder","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With the kind enum in place, you can write a recursive-descent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser that emits into a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":". The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"builder accepts a stream of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"startNode"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"token"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"staticToken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"\/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finishNode"},{"type":"text","text":" calls and produces a green tree whose structure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mirrors the calls one-for-one."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/02-DriveBuilder","estimatedTime":"25min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/02-drivebuilder"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/01-DefineLanguage":{"title":"Define the Calculator Language","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Every Cambium grammar starts with a kind enumeration: one case per"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"token and one per node the parser can produce. The kind enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"becomes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Kind"},{"type":"text","text":" associated type of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conformance, and Cambium specializes its generic types around that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"language to make tree storage compact and traversal type-safe."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","estimatedTime":"15min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/01-definelanguage"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery":{"title":"Add Precedence and Error Recovery","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The parser from the previous tutorial handles only “atomic”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prefix forms — literals and parenthesized groups. To parse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1 + 2 * 3"},{"type":"text","text":" correctly the parser needs operator precedence; to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"survive "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1 +"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(2"},{"type":"text","text":" it needs error recovery."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery","estimatedTime":"30min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/03-precedenceandrecovery"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/04-ReadingTree":{"title":"Read the Tree Without Allocating","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Cambium tree is meant to be queried frequently — by IDEs on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"every keystroke, by analyzers walking every node, by formatters"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"emitting bytes. To stay within reasonable memory and ARC"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"budgets the primary traversal API is borrowed: walks happen"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"type":"text","text":" cursors handed to a closure, and source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text is exposed as a chunk-streaming view rather than a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"materialized "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/04-ReadingTree","estimatedTime":"25min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/04-readingtree"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/06-Evaluator":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/06-evaluator","title":"Evaluate the Typed AST","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With the typed AST in place from Tutorial 5, an evaluator"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"becomes a recursive function that pattern-matches on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ExprSyntax"},{"type":"text","text":". Each kind has a closed structure — its operands"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and operator are addressable through the typed accessors —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so the evaluator stays small and total."}],"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/06-Evaluator","kind":"project","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"20min"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/TableOfContents":{"url":"\/tutorials\/tableofcontents","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recursive-descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fork-join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization."}],"role":"overview","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","kind":"overview","type":"topic"},"https://github.com/daig/cambium/tree/main/Examples/Calculator":{"title":"Examples\/Calculator","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","type":"link"},"https://github.com/daig/cambium/blob/main/Examples/Calculator/README.md":{"title":"README.md","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"README.md"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","type":"link"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/09-AnalysisTranslation":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/09-analysistranslation","title":"Translate Analysis Across Edits","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The witnesses you built in Tutorial 7 (replacement) and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Tutorial 8 (reparse) exist to make analysis caches "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"survive"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edits"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Without translation every keystroke would invalidate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"every memoized value — defeating the whole point of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incremental tool."}],"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/09-AnalysisTranslation","kind":"project","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"30min"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/11-ParallelParse":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/11-parallelparse","title":"Parallel Parsing with Shared Interning","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel parsing splits work across worker tasks: each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"worker parses an independent subtree concurrently, then a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"master builder splices the worker results into one logical"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tree. The correctness-critical question is how the workers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"share token-text vocabulary and the green-node namespace."}],"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/11-ParallelParse","kind":"project","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"25min"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/10-ForkJoinEval":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/10-forkjoineval","title":"Fork-Join Evaluation Across Tasks","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":". Cambium’s red"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layer realizes lazily under lock-free atomic slots, so two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tasks descending into different siblings of the same parent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"never observe inconsistent state. The typed AST overlays are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable, Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":", so passing a sub-expression to a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child task is just an argument pass."}],"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/10-ForkJoinEval","kind":"project","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"25min"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/07-ReplacementWitnesses":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/07-replacementwitnesses","title":"Replace Subtrees with Witnesses","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium trees are persistent: there is no in-place mutation."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)"},{"type":"text","text":" produces a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"new"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tree that shares as much green storage with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the old as possible, and returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" describing the structural"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"change."}],"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/07-ReplacementWitnesses","kind":"project","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"25min"}}}